{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Publish an updated 'Tackling Loneliness' strategy & funding for programmes",
        "additional_details": "We think loneliness is a silent epidemic, it holds no bias as to who it affects - young or old, male or female.\r\n \r\nWe think the 2018 strategy lacks sufficient updates to address the evolving crisis, exacerbated by post-pandemic isolation, economic pressures, and the decline of community spaces.\r\n \r\nWe are calling for an updated strategy in this Parliament, with dedicated funding for community programs, mental health support, and awareness campaigns to combat this growing public health crisis.",
        "background": "Seven years and four governments ago, the-then Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) published its 'A connected society: a strategy for tackling loneliness' policy paper that subsequently reported every year until 2023.",
